Review: My brain works the exact same way as Sherlock’s except I get all of the predictions wrong
Most delightful movie of 2023? I am CHEESING!!!! And blushing… 😳 and turning British?!? 💂‍♀️

Solid directorial debut for my handsome boy Nick Miller (from the mean streets of Chicago). It’s never laugh out loud funny, but it’s consistently entertaining and the film contains a number of solid gags/jokes.
Loooove a movie that vaguely feels like Bioshock. And Kurt Russell so dreamy!
The deepest, darkest pits of “he’s literally me” …. It’s important that I go outside today I think
Ehhhhh almost something. Rachel Weisz at her hottest, perhaps? Maybe that’s enough..
I love not understanding stop motion animation. I fucking love it
I think a future second viewing will probably open me up to this a bit more than the initial viewing, but still very tender and heartbreaking.
Tinnnnnny bit too long. Otherwise love
